As published in the August 31 USDA Nationwide waivers, School Food Authorities (SFAs) may choose to provide meal service under the Summer Food Service Program (SFSP) through December 31, 2020 (subject to available funding) or continue the National School Lunch Program (NSLP) and School Breakfast Program (SBP).

Nashua-Plainfield Community School District is participating in this program until December 31, 2020 or until the funding runs out! Starting with today Sept. 8, 2020 as day 1 for free breakfast and lunch meals to every student in our district. Meals will be provided to all children without charge and are the same for all children regardless of race, color, national origin, sex, age or disabilty, and there will be no discrimination in the course of the meal service.

Thank you and have a great day!

Information from our Transportation Director:

Plainfield Parents...the Nashua-Plainfield Shuttle Bus will pick up students at Busy B Daycare at approximately 745am each day. The bus will also pick up students on the North side of the Plainfield School at approximately 750am.
After school, the Nashua-Plainfield Shuttle Bus will drop students at Busy B Daycare at approximately 355pm and the Plainfield School at approximately 4pm.
These times are approximate. Please be ready 5 minutes before the scheduled stop and be prepared to wait up to 5 minutes after the scheduled stop.
Please have siblings/family members or daycare kids sit together in seats.
There will be hand sanitizer available for students to use when loading and unloading.
All NP buses will be sanitized after each bus route and activity.
If you have any questions, please send me a message.
Share this information with any NP parents in the Plainfield area.

The Nashua-Plainfield Community School District is seeking:

Substitute Teachers in Grades PreK-12 for the 2020-2021 school year.

The following criteria is being used by the Iowa Board of Educational Examiners to receive your substitute license from the State of Iowa.

*You must be 20 years of age or older.
*You must have an AA Degree with 60 Hours of Completion.
*You must take a short course through Central Rivers AEA on Substitute Teaching.
*If you have a paraprofessional license you may apply for a substitute license after you take the substitute course from Central Rivers AEA.
*You must have a current substitute license from the Iowa Board of Educational Examiners or a provisional substitute license.

Please contact Mr. Scott Striegel at 641-435-4166 or sstriegel@nashua-plainfield.k12.ia.us or Mrs. Shannon Wurzer at 641-435-4114 or swurzer@nashua-plainfield.k12.ia.us, if you are interested in applying.

The Nashua-Plainfield Community School district is an equal employment opportunity, affirmative action employer.

post_text:
This is the email that Mr. Turner sent all families today:

Parents and Stakeholders of the Nashua-Plainfield Schools

An overview of the Health and Safety Plan for On-Site, Hybrid, and Remote Learning is attached. There will be more specifics attached to the school website on each plan. The secondary students' first day of class will be August 24 and the elementary on August 25. The elementary will conduct intake conferences on the 24th as they have in past years.

Our commitment remains getting all of our students to school every day safely. The decision to move to a hybrid plan will be based on local health data and in consultation with Iowa public health. The hybrid model we have developed places an emphasis on getting our youngest, elementary learners to school on a daily basis and will involve keeping kids in pods to contain any possible exposures so that we can avoid an overall school shutdown.

Thank you for your patience and flexibility in working with the district through these times. We will keep you informed as conditions warrant.

Sincerely,

Keith Turner

post_text:
Parents,

I wanted to update you on guidance for the "Return to Learn" plan. The document that I have attached is an overview created by the district leadership team. Over the next week we will update district patrons in more detail concerning health and safety provisions as well as our hybrid learning plan. It is still the intention of the district to run regular classes for all students everyday at the beginning of the year. However, because the situation is so fluid, we know we have to be ready to teach in all three plans: face to face, hybrid, and distance learning.

For those families who do not wish for their children to return in person, the school district will provide at-home virtual learning. Those families still need to enroll their students to receive education in this manner.

Keith Turner
Superintendent, Nashua-Plainfield

It truly is incredible what students from a small rural school have accomplished in this arena and that is a testament to their leader. #HuskyNProud #NHD2020

May 20 at 3:31 PM ·

The boards of the IGHSAU and Iowa High School Athletic Association have approved the start of summer softball and baseball practice on June 1, following today’s proclamation from Governor Kim Reynolds and guidance from the Iowa Department of Education. Contests can begin no earlier than June 15. Further sport-specific guidance will be released early next week.

shared_text:
Origami Optimism
April 3 at 2:07 PM ·

Being stuck in your houses, we wanted to provide a way for you to still be able to fold paper cranes. Our goal is to get 1,000 cranes folded before May 1st!

We have two places for you to pick up paper and drop off finished cranes: Jayne Levi’s house (324 Douglas Street, Nashua) and Taylor Wedeking’s house (520 Main Street, Plainfield). There are pictures below of where the box is located at each home. Remember, after you pick up paper or drop off cranes, wash your hands!

Folding cranes is a great activity to do for kids and adults! If you need help folding, there are links at the bottom of this post to helpful sources. You can also message this page, and we can work out a different way to help you learn how to fold!

Post pictures of you and your families folding cranes and tag us in it so we can see everyone! We can’t wait to see how many cranes are folded! Good luck!

Pictures: https://www.wikihow.com/Fold-a-Paper-Crane
Video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KfnyopxdJXQ

post_text:
Good Afternoon,

As we are all aware, this is ever-changing, evolving situation. The Nashua-Plainfield Administration is deeply committed to keeping all stakeholders informed as much as possible. In an attempt to do this, we are sharing a COVID 19 Frequently Asked Questions document to address some of the more common questions that we have been receiving. The FAQ can be found here: https://docs.google.com/document/d/1ybeHsq8eOZL2N4PZXfYYOuBrwC3FRjM81qAYC-VwasU/edit?usp=sharing

We want to make families aware of a great scholarship opportunity for high school seniors. All students need to do is complete a FAFSA and enroll as a full-time student in the fall. For more information, visit www.iowacollegeaid.gov/LastDollar.

post_text: Congratulations to Nashua-Plainfield senior Jayne Levi for being selected as a candidate for the U.S. Presidential Scholar Award! She was one of only 70 Iowa seniors nominated by the director of the Iowa Department of Education for this honor. Nationwide, 4500 students are selected from 3.6 million seniors as candidates for the award. This group will be reduced to 600 semi-finalists in April and then to 161 finalists who will visit the White House for an award ceremony with the President in June. #HuskyNProud

Cedar Falls Community Foundation
January 16 at 9:00 AM ·

Morgan Kapping was one of several UNI students who received the CFCF Robert Eller Study Abroad Scholarship for Fall 2019. Morgan studied at the American College of Greece in Athens. During her breaks, she enjoyed trips to Ireland, Croatia, and Italy. She visited the Cliffs of Moher, the famous waterfalls in Bosnia (which closely borders Croatia) and some of the most famous monuments in Italy.

Sunday Oct 27th at 5:30pm NP YSF football game is at home. Many of you know Kevin Potratz, what most dont know this is his last game he will announce for NP football. Unfortunately Kevin is retiring. If you heard his voice on the field as a kid, show up and bring dog treats. EVERYONE, LETS FILL A TRUCK OF DOG TREATS! SPREAD THE WORD!!

post_text:
The 2nd grade students have been talking about how kids can make a difference, learning about matter in science and how it changes and studying money. The students came up with a bake sale to showcase what they have learned. The 2nd grade class has decided that all funds will go to the University of Iowa Stead Family Children's Hospital. Please come out and support them, as they have worked very hard getting ready for this! Yesterday, they came to the high school to use the kitchen to bake!

The bake sale will be open to Junior high and high school students tomorrow during homeroom (2:45-3:25). It was also be available at the elementary school open to the public form 2:45 - 3:00. Free will donations will also be taken.

Thank you for your support!

Interested in becoming a substitute teacher?

For those with a four-year degree (or para-educator license) who wish to become authorized to be a substitute teacher, there will be a class offered October 25-27, 2019 in the W-SR Middle School Media Center. Classes will be 5-8 PM on Friday, then 8 AM-5 PM on both Saturday and Sunday.

In order to register you will need to go to: aealearning.truenorthlogic.com Then go to course # 3405 - Section 2722385. Any difficulties registering please contact the AEA at: 319-273-8200

If it is something you're interested in, make sure to get yourself registered right away.

If you have any questions feel free to reach out to the Peggy Slattery (peggy.slattery@wsr.k12.ia.us),

Online Registration OPENS today at 4:00 pm!

Parents of all returning students, Kindergarten through 12th, will need to complete the 2019-2020 school year registration process online. Online registration opens on Tuesday, August 6 at 4:00 pm. Please complete the online registration process by Aug. 13, 2019. Forms and payments are due August 13th. Registration is not complete until payments are made.

If you have a JMC parent account already set-up, please click the link below, log-in, and follow the online registration steps:

https://nashua-plainfield.onlinejmc.com/Parent/Login.aspx?ReturnUrl=%2fParent%2f

New students and families new to the Nashua-Plainfield School District should contact Val Roach at 641-435-4835 for registration information (if you have not already received a packet).

You will need a JMC parent account to register online. Please email vroach@nashua-plainfield.k12.ia.us to obtain your parent password.
